      <TYPE> FUNCTION VAL_MUL<T>( BAD, ARG1, ARG2, STATUS )
*+
*  Name:
*     VAL_MUL<T>

*  Purpose:
*     Perform a <COMM> multiplication operation.

*  Language:
*     Starlink Fortran

*  Invocation:
*     RESULT = VAL_MUL<T>( BAD, ARG1, ARG2, STATUS )

*  Description:
*     The routine performs an arithmetic multiplication operation between
*     a pair of arguments of type <COMM>.  If a numerical error occurs,
*     the value VAL__BAD<T> is returned and a STATUS value is set.

*  Arguments:
*     BAD = LOGICAL (Given)
*        Whether the argument values (ARG1 & ARG2) may be "bad".
*     ARG1, ARG2 = <TYPE> (Given)
*        The two <COMM> arguments for the multiplication operation.
*     STATUS = INTEGER (Given & Returned)
*        This should be set to SAI__OK on entry, otherwise the routine
*        returns immediately with the result VAL__BAD<T>.  A STATUS
*        value will be set by this routine if a numerical error occurs.

*  Returned Value:
*     VAL_MUL<T> = <TYPE>
*        Returns the result of the multiplication operation as a value of
*        type <COMM>.  The value returned is:
*
*           VAL_MUL<T> = ARG1 * ARG2
*
*        The value VAL__BAD<T> will be returned under error conditions.

